<div class="articleBody">
        
    
                                                                                <p>
                    From a spare, second-floor office in Queens, an outpost of the Ecuadorean government offers English classes, computer training and after-school programs to immigrants building new lives in New York City. But these days, the office&rsquo;s busiest program works in the opposite direction &mdash; helping Ecuadoreans go home.        </p>
                                                </div>
<div class="articleInline runaroundLeft">
    						<div class="inlineImage module">
	<div class="image">
		         <div class="icon enlargeThis"><a href="javascript:pop_me_up2('http://www.nytimes.com/imagepages/2010/12/03/ECUADOR.html','ECUADOR_html','width=720,height=563,scrollbars=yes,toolbars=no,resizable=yes')">Enlarge This Image</a></div>
